SIMPLE: rightly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rightly
<hw>Right"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>richtlice</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Straightly; directly; in
front.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>According to justice; according to the divine will
or moral rectitude; uprightly; <as>as, duty <ex>rightly</ex>
performed</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Properly; fitly; suitably; appropriately.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Eve <qex>rightly</qex> called, Mother of all mankind.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>According to truth or fact; correctly; not
erroneously; exactly.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧I can not <xex>rightly</xex>
say.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou didst not <qex>rightly</qex> see.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Right-minded</ent>⟦br⟧
